{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Researchers who looked at doctor-assisted deaths in the Netherlands found that some patients had declined treatment that might have helped.", "abstract": "Study published in journal JAMA Psychiatry, examining doctor-assisted deaths in Netherlands, finds many cases in which patients refused helpful treatments and attributed their desire to die to loneliness; results are expected to affect current debate in several countries over whether right to choose doctor-assisted suicide should be extended to psychiatric cases; United States restricts practice to mentally competent adults with terminal diseases.", "section_name": "Health", "print_page": "6", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Benedict", "role": "reported", "lastname": "CAREY", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By BENEDICT CAREY"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/11/health/assisted-suicide-mental-disorders.html", "lead_paragraph": "Researchers who looked at doctor-assisted deaths in the Netherlands found that some patients had declined treatment that might have helped.", "headline": {"main": "Assisted Suicide Study Questions Its Use for Mentally Ill", "print_headline": "Study Questions the Use of Doctor-Assisted Death"}, "_id": "56bb867238f0d862fbbcec76", "word_count": "827", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/02/11/science/11DEPRESSION/11DEPRESSION-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/02/11/science/11DEPRESSION/11DEPRESSION-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2016/02/11/science/11DEPRESSION/11DEPRESSION-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/02/11/science/11DEPRESSION/11DEPRESSION-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2016/02/11/science/11DEPRESSION/11DEPRESSION-thumbSta